text: Georgiyevskoye () is a rural locality (a selo) in Sergiyevskoye Rural Settlement of Giaginsky District, Adygea, Russia. The population was 238 as of 2018. There are 5 streets. == Geography == The village is located 6 km south- west from Sergiyevskoye, 39 km south-east from Giaginskaya and 34 km north- east from Maykop. == Ethnicity == The village is inhabited by Russians, Armenians, Chuvashes. == References == Category:Rural localities in Giaginsky District
title: Georgiyevskoye, Republic of Adygea
